H0.text: Egg, nymph, pupa, adult is the series that shows the stages of complete metamorphosis for many insects.

H1.text: Egg, larva, nymph, adult is the series that correctly shows the stages of complete metamorphosis for many insects.

H2.text: Egg, nymph 1, nymph 2, adult is the series that shows the stages of complete metamorphosis for many insects.

H3.text: Egg, larva, pupa, adult are the stages of complete metamorphosis that many insects go through.

A4.text: In holometabolous insects, immature stages are called larvae and differ markedly from adults. Insects which undergo holometabolism pass through a larval stage, then enter an inactive state called pupa (called a 'chrysalis' in butterfly species), and finally emerge as adults.

A5.text: In hemimetabolous insects, immature stages are called nymphs.
